let _markdown = "\n\n# HiChIP Analysis with CLI\n\nThis tutorial provides a comprehensive guide to analyzing HiChIP data using the Chr3D command-line interface.\n\n## Pipeline Overview\n\n<Mermaid\n  chart={`flowchart LR\n  subgraph Input[\"Input Files\"]\n      F1[R1.fastq.gz]\n      F2[R2.fastq.gz]\n      G[genome.fa]\n      R[restriction_sites.bed]\n  end\n\n  subgraph CLI[\"chr3d run --mode hichip\"]\n      S1[Step 1: Skip Linker]\n      S2[Step 2: Mapping]\n      S3[Step 3: Purifying]\n      S4[Step 4: Categorization]\n      S5[Step 5: Peak Calling]\n      S6[Step 6: Loop Calling]\n      S1 --> S2 --> S3 --> S4 --> S5\n      S4 --> S6\n  end\n\n  subgraph Output[\"Output Files\"]\n      O1[mapped.bedpe]\n      O2[purified.bedpe]\n      O3[categorized.ipet/spet]\n      O4[peaks.narrowPeak]\n      O5[loops.FDRfiltered.txt]\n  end\n\n  F1 --> CLI\n  F2 --> CLI\n  G --> CLI\n  R --> CLI\n  CLI --> Output\n\n  style Input fill:#e8f5e9\n  style CLI fill:#e3f2fd\n  style Output fill:#fff3e0\n`}\n/>\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# Run complete HiChIP pipeline\nchr3d run --mode hichip \\\n    --fastq-r1 sample_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 sample_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /ref/hg38.fa \\\n    --restriction-sites /ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed \\\n    --output-dir ./hichip_output \\\n    --threads 8 \\\n    --sample-id my_sample\n```\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n### 1. Generate Restriction Sites File\n\nBefore running HiChIP analysis, you need a restriction sites file for your enzyme:\n\n```bash\n# Generate MboI restriction sites for hg38\nchr3d generate-sites \\\n    --genome /ref/hg38.fa \\\n    --enzyme MboI \\\n    --output /ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed\n```\n\n**Common Restriction Enzymes:**\n\n| Enzyme  | Recognition Site | Command            |\n| ------- | ---------------- | ------------------ |\n| MboI    | GATC             | `--enzyme MboI`    |\n| DpnII   | GATC             | `--enzyme DpnII`   |\n| HindIII | AAGCTT           | `--enzyme HindIII` |\n\n### 2. Index Reference Genome\n\n```bash\n# Create BWA index (if not already done)\nbwa index /ref/hg38.fa\n```\n\n## Complete Command Reference\n\n```bash\nchr3d run --mode hichip \\\n    --fastq-r1 <R1.fastq.gz> \\\n    --fastq-r2 <R2.fastq.gz> \\\n    --genome-index <genome.fa> \\\n    --restriction-sites <sites.bed> \\\n    --output-dir <output_directory> \\\n    [OPTIONS]\n```\n\n### Required Arguments\n\n| Argument              | Description                             |\n| --------------------- | --------------------------------------- |\n| `--fastq-r1`          | Input R1 FASTQ file (gzipped supported) |\n| `--fastq-r2`          | Input R2 FASTQ file (gzipped supported) |\n| `--genome-index`      | BWA-indexed reference genome FASTA      |\n| `--restriction-sites` | Restriction sites BED file              |\n| `--output-dir`        | Output directory                        |\n\n### Optional Arguments\n\n| Argument               | Default | Description                    |\n| ---------------------- | ------- | ------------------------------ |\n| `--threads`            | 24      | Number of threads              |\n| `--sample-id`          | sample  | Sample identifier              |\n| `--use-bwa-mem`        | False   | Use BWA-MEM (recommended)      |\n| `--genome-size`        | hs      | Genome size for MACS3          |\n| `--mapping-quality`    | 30      | Minimum mapping quality        |\n| `--extension-length`   | 500     | Tag extension for clustering   |\n| `--ipet-threshold`     | 2       | Minimum iPET count for loops   |\n| `--fdr-cutoff`         | 0.05    | FDR threshold for significance |\n| `--keep-intermediates` | False   | Keep intermediate files        |\n\n## Step-by-Step Execution\n\n### Full Example with All Options\n\n```bash\nchr3d run --mode hichip \\\n    --fastq-r1 /data/H3K27ac_HiChIP_R1.fastq.gz \\\n    --fastq-r2 /data/H3K27ac_HiChIP_R2.fastq.gz \\\n    --genome-index /ref/hg38.fa \\\n    --restriction-sites /ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed \\\n    --output-dir /output/hichip_analysis \\\n    --threads 16 \\\n    --sample-id H3K27ac_GM12878 \\\n    --use-bwa-mem \\\n    --genome-size hs \\\n    --mapping-quality 30 \\\n    --extension-length 500 \\\n    --ipet-threshold 2 \\\n    --fdr-cutoff 0.05 \\\n    --keep-intermediates\n```\n\n## Output Directory Structure\n\nAfter running the pipeline, your output directory will contain:\n\n```\noutput_dir/\n├── step1_linker_filtering/     # Empty (HiChIP skips linker filtering)\n│\n├── step2_mapping/\n│   ├── mapped.sam              # Raw alignment (if --keep-intermediates)\n│   ├── mapped.sorted.bam       # Sorted BAM\n│   ├── mapped.dedup.bedpe      # Deduplicated PETs\n│   └── mapping_stats.txt       # Alignment statistics\n│\n├── step3_purifying/\n│   ├── purified.valid.bedpe    # Valid inter-fragment PETs\n│   └── purified.sameres.bedpe  # Removed same-fragment PETs\n│\n├── step4_categorization/\n│   ├── categorized.ipet        # Inter-ligation PETs (for loops)\n│   ├── categorized.spet        # Self-ligation PETs (for peaks)\n│   └── categorized.opet        # Other PETs\n│\n├── step5_peaks/\n│   ├── peaks_peaks.narrowPeak  # Called peaks\n│   ├── peaks_summits.bed       # Peak summits\n│   └── peaks_peaks.xls         # Peak statistics\n│\n├── step6_loops/\n│   ├── loops.cluster.filtered          # All loops (iPET &gt;= threshold)\n│   └── loops.cluster.FDRfiltered.txt   # Significant loops (FDR &lt; cutoff)\n│\n└── pipeline.log                # Complete pipeline log\n```\n\n## Pipeline Steps Explained\n\n### Step 1: Linker Filtering (SKIPPED)\n\n**Important**: HiChIP does NOT use linker sequences. The CLI automatically skips this step for HiChIP mode.\n\n```\nLog output:\nSTEP 1: SKIPPED (HiChIP does not use linkers)\n```\n\n### Step 2: Genomic Mapping\n\nMaps paired-end reads to the reference genome using BWA.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  STEP 2: MAPPING                                                 │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  R1.fastq.gz ─┐                                                 │\n│               ├──► BWA-MEM ──► SAM ──► BAM ──► BEDPE            │\n│  R2.fastq.gz ─┘                                                 │\n│                                                                  │\n│  Key operations:                                                 │\n│  • Align reads to reference genome                               │\n│  • Convert SAM to sorted BAM                                     │\n│  • Remove PCR duplicates                                         │\n│  • Generate BEDPE format                                         │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Step 3: PET Purifying\n\nRemoves same-fragment PETs using restriction site information.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  STEP 3: PURIFYING                                               │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  For each PET:                                                   │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │ Read1 ──────────────────────────────── Read2            │    │\n│  │   │                                       │             │    │\n│  │   ▼                                       ▼             │    │\n│  │ Fragment A                           Fragment B         │    │\n│  │   │                                       │             │    │\n│  │   └───────────── Compare ─────────────────┘             │    │\n│  │                     │                                   │    │\n│  │         ┌───────────┴───────────┐                       │    │\n│  │         ▼                       ▼                       │    │\n│  │   Same Fragment?          Different?                    │    │\n│  │         │                       │                       │    │\n│  │         ▼                       ▼                       │    │\n│  │   REMOVE (artifact)       KEEP (valid)                  │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Step 4: PET Categorization\n\nClassifies PETs based on genomic distance.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  STEP 4: CATEGORIZATION                                          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  Distance cutoff for HiChIP: 1000bp                              │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │                                                          │    │\n│  │  Distance &gt; 1kb?  ──YES──►  iPET (loops)                │    │\n│  │       │                                                  │    │\n│  │      NO                                                  │    │\n│  │       │                                                  │    │\n│  │       ▼                                                  │    │\n│  │  Distance ≤ 1kb?  ──YES──►  sPET (peaks)                │    │\n│  │       │                                                  │    │\n│  │      NO                                                  │    │\n│  │       │                                                  │    │\n│  │       ▼                                                  │    │\n│  │  Invalid?  ───────YES──►  oPET (discard)                │    │\n│  │                                                          │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Step 5: Peak Calling\n\nCalls enrichment peaks from self-ligation PETs using MACS3.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  STEP 5: PEAK CALLING                                            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  Input: categorized.spet                                         │\n│                                                                  │\n│  MACS3 callpeak:                                                 │\n│  • Genome size: hs (human)                                       │\n│  • Q-value cutoff: 0.05                                          │\n│  • Keep duplicates: all                                          │\n│                                                                  │\n│  Output:                                                         │\n│  • peaks_peaks.narrowPeak (peak coordinates)                     │\n│  • peaks_summits.bed (peak summits)                              │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Step 6: Loop Calling\n\nIdentifies significant chromatin loops with statistical testing.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  STEP 6: LOOP CALLING                                            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  6.1 Pre-clustering:                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │  Extend each tag by 500bp based on strand                │    │\n│  │  Forward (+): extend upstream                            │    │\n│  │  Reverse (-): extend downstream                          │    │\n│  │  Group overlapping tags into clusters                    │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                  │\n│  6.2 Anchor clustering:                                          │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │  Merge clusters where BOTH anchors overlap               │    │\n│  │  Iterate until no more merges possible                   │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                  │\n│  6.3 Statistical significance:                                   │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │  Distance-corrected Poisson test (HiChIP-specific)       │    │\n│  │  Benjamini-Hochberg FDR correction                       │    │\n│  │  Filter: FDR &lt; 0.05                                      │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                                                                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Example Log Output\n\n```\n======================================================================\nChr3D HiChIP Pipeline\n======================================================================\nSample ID: H3K27ac_GM12878\nMode: hichip\nThreads: 16\n\nSTEP 1: SKIPPED (HiChIP does not use linkers)\n\n======================================================================\nSTEP 2: GENOMIC MAPPING\n======================================================================\nRunning BWA-MEM alignment...\n  Total read pairs: 100,000,000\n  Mapped pairs: 95,234,567\n  Unique PETs: 78,456,789\n  Duplicate rate: 17.6%\n\n======================================================================\nSTEP 3: PET PURIFYING\n======================================================================\nLoading restriction sites...\n  Loaded 1,234,567 MboI fragments\nProcessing PETs...\n  Total PETs: 78,456,789\n  Valid PETs: 43,492,345\n  Same-fragment removed: 34,964,444\n  Valid ratio: 55.4%\n\n======================================================================\nSTEP 4: PET CATEGORIZATION\n======================================================================\nCategorizing PETs...\n  Total PETs: 43,492,345\n  iPETs: 24,771,234 (57.0%)\n  sPETs: 385,678 (0.9%)\n  oPETs: 18,335,433 (42.1%)\n\n======================================================================\nSTEP 5: PEAK CALLING\n======================================================================\nRunning MACS3...\n  Peaks called: 45,678\n\n======================================================================\nSTEP 6: LOOP CALLING\n======================================================================\nStep 6.1: Pre-clustering...\n  Pre-clusters: 1,234,567\nStep 6.2: Anchor clustering...\n  Anchor clusters: 567,890\nStep 6.3: Statistical significance...\n  Loops tested: 567,890\n  Significant loops (FDR &lt; 0.05): 12,345\n\n======================================================================\nPIPELINE COMPLETE\n======================================================================\nOutput directory: /output/hichip_analysis\nSignificant loops: /output/hichip_analysis/step6_loops/loops.cluster.FDRfiltered.txt\n```\n\n## Output File Formats\n\n### Loops File (loops.cluster.FDRfiltered.txt)\n\nTab-separated file with significant chromatin loops:\n\n```\nchr1    100000    100500    chr1    200000    200500    5    2.3    100000    0.001    0.023\nchr1    300000    300500    chr1    450000    450500    8    3.1    150000    0.0001   0.005\n```\n\n| Column | Description                         |\n| ------ | ----------------------------------- |\n| 1-3    | Anchor 1: chromosome, start, end    |\n| 4-6    | Anchor 2: chromosome, start, end    |\n| 7      | iPET count (observed)               |\n| 8      | Expected count (distance-corrected) |\n| 9      | Distance between anchors            |\n| 10     | Raw p-value                         |\n| 11     | FDR (adjusted p-value)              |\n\n### Peaks File (peaks\\_peaks.narrowPeak)\n\nStandard ENCODE narrowPeak format:\n\n| Column | Description        |\n| ------ | ------------------ |\n| 1      | Chromosome         |\n| 2      | Start              |\n| 3      | End                |\n| 4      | Peak name          |\n| 5      | Score              |\n| 6      | Strand             |\n| 7      | Signal value       |\n| 8      | -log10(p-value)    |\n| 9      | -log10(q-value)    |\n| 10     | Peak summit offset |\n\n## Quality Metrics\n\n**Good HiChIP Data:**\n\n* Mapping rate: >70%\n* Cis ratio: >60%\n* Valid PET ratio: >50%\n* iPET percentage: >40%\n\n**Warning Signs:**\n\n* Low cis ratio (\\<40%): May indicate ligation issues\n* High same-fragment rate (>50%): Incomplete digestion\n* Few peaks: Low enrichment or wrong antibody\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### No restriction sites file\n\n```bash\n# Generate restriction sites first\nchr3d generate-sites --genome /ref/hg38.fa --enzyme MboI --output /ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed\n```\n\n### High same-fragment rate\n\n* Check restriction enzyme digestion efficiency\n* Verify restriction sites file matches your enzyme\n* Consider re-digestion or protocol optimization\n\n### No significant loops\n\n* Increase sequencing depth\n* Lower FDR threshold for exploration: `--fdr-cutoff 0.1`\n* Check if peaks are present (loops anchor at peaks)\n\n### Memory issues\n\n* Reduce threads: `--threads 4`\n* Process smaller batches\n* Use `--keep-intermediates` to debug step-by-step\n\n## See Also\n\n* [HiChIP API Tutorial](./hichip-api) - Python API version\n* [HiChIP CLI Reference](../cli/hichip) - Complete CLI documentation\n* [Hi-C CLI Tutorial](./hic-cli) - Hi-C analysis tutorial\n";
